Name: ns_regcode
Author: n00bie
Category: NickServ
Last updated: 2007-08-16T14:04:28+01:00

This module splits the nick registration process into 2 steps. The first after giving the registration command will give out a passcode. The passcode must be supplied using the PROCEED or CONFIRM command in order to complete the registration.
====================================================================
Example:
-NickServ- To complete your registration you need to enter a passcode.
-NickServ- Type: [b]/msg NickServ PROCEED [u]passcode[/u][/b]
-NickServ- Your passcode is: JrYH8rCpz
====================================================================
[b]NOTE:[/b] Do NOT use this module if you have [b]NSEmailReg[/b] enabled on your network. It is designed for network who don\'t used or have UseMail facilities.

[b]Providing command:[/b]
/msg NickServ PROCEED passcode
/msg NickServ CONFIRM passcode

====================================================================
This module have no configurable option.

Version 1.0.0 supports Anope 1.7.18
Version 2.0.0 supports Anope 1.7.21
Version 2.0.0~1 supports Anope 1.8.5
